    {
      "id": "1491452895370019036",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-08T17:01:20.111+02:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "`CWallet` es la clase principal para Wallets en Bitcoin Core. Dentro de sus responsabilidades están: Trackear balances, firmar transacciones, manejar descriptors y keys, etc.\n\nSegún achow101 (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34861#discussion_r2998212485) la idea es no extender la clase (o tal vez los ficheros wallet.cpp o wallet.h) más de lo que está.",
      "author": {
        "id": "267078046857560065",
        "name": "roundtripoor",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": ">",
        "color": "#992D22",
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [
          {
            "id": "1483542958153138197",
            "name": "PR Proposer",
            "color": "#992D22",
            "position": 1
          }
        ],
        "avatarUrl": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/267078046857560065/b7cdeba78d812e377a3a87399fe32b33.png?size=512"
      },
      "attachments": [],
